parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to serious injury or fatality in the event of an accident, as the airbags may not deploy or may deploy unexpectedly.
symptoms: The service airbag indicator illuminates consistently
airbags fail to deploy in the event of an accident
passenger airbag does not activate when a passenger is seated
airbag sensor does not register the presence of a passenger.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The problems with the transmission and transfer case can cause the vehicle to jerk, shudder, or lose power, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle jerks or shudders heavily when accelerating
the vehicle bucks or shutters at certain speeds
the "Reduce Engine Speed" warning appears on the dashboard
the vehicle will not let you drive over a certain speed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transfer case chain can cause the vehicle to lose power, jerk, or shudder, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The chain in the transfer case becomes loose
the chain skips on the sprockets
the vehicle jerks or shudders when accelerating
the vehicle may roll backwards uphill while trying to accelerate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the accelerator pedal sensor can cause the vehicle to decelerate independently, fail to respond to accelerator pedal input, or even accelerate unexpectedly, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The "Reduce Engine Speed" warning message illuminates
the accelerator pedal is depressed but the vehicle fails to respond
